  "text": "Hepatic phenotypes of HOXB7-Cre driven Vhlh knockout mice are Hif-2α-dependent Previous conditional knockout mice with Vhlh inactivation in hepatocytes developed liver hemangiomas and erythrocytosis, but no hemangioma-associated extramedullary erythropoiesis [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . In those mouse models, hemangiomas and erythrocytosis were rescued by Hif-2α inactivation. We therefore examined the effects of Hif-2α inactivation on the phenotypes observed in our mouse model by generating HOXB7-Cre; Vhlh fl/fl ; Hif-2α fl/fl double knockouts. Hif-2α knockout rescued elevated serum Epo (Fig. 3b ) as well as extramedullary erythropoiesis, as assessed with colony forming unit assay (Fig. 2b) . Hif-2α inactivation also ameliorated the hemangioma phenotype. The onset of hemangiomas was delayed (25 % vs 90 % at 6 weeks), and the number of hemangiomas per liver was significantly reduced in 2 to 3-month old double knockouts (Fig. 3d ). ",
